decks.notes: The main focus of this deck is to quickly mill out the opponent's library by playing cards that force them to mill cards from the top of their deck, such as Ruin Crab, Hedron Crab, and Archive Trap. The deck also includes cards like Tasha's Hideous Laughter and Surgical Extraction to help speed up the milling process. With the combination of efficient mill cards and control elements like Jace, the Perfected Mind and Snapcaster Mage, this deck aims to overwhelm the opponent by emptying their library before they can win through conventional means.

This control deck aims to dominate the game through counter spells and removal, using cards like Force of Negation, Counterspell, and Subtlety to control the board. The deck also utilizes powerful planeswalkers like Teferi, Time Raveler and powerful finishers like The One Ring and Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury to secure victory. The deck focuses on disrupting the opponent's game plan, while setting up its own win condition to come out on top in the matchup.

This deck focuses on controlling the game by using powerful Eldrazi creatures and spells to disrupt the opponent's strategy. It aims to ramp up mana quickly with cards like Utopia Sprawl and Eldrazi Temple to cast big threats like Emrakul, the Promised End and World Breaker. Kozilek's Return and Kozilek's Command provide additional removal, while Ancient Stirrings helps find key pieces. The deck also includes The One Ring to help dominate the late game. Overall, the deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with its controlling Eldrazi strategy.

The main focus of this deck is to control the game with powerful counterspells and removal spells while utilizing The One Ring as a win condition. The deck is designed to disrupt your opponent's game plan, protect your own board, and eventually overwhelm them with the powerful effects of The One Ring. This Boros Aggro deck focuses on quickly overwhelming opponents with aggressive creatures and burn spells. The key concept of the deck is to maintain board control through cards like Static Prison and Blood Moon while applying pressure with fast creatures like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Bonecrusher Giant. Additionally, utilizing Ajani, Nacatl Pariah and Fable of the Mirror-Breaker can provide additional ways to boost your creatures and push for lethal damage. The inclusion of Jegantha, the Wellspring as a companion adds an extra layer of flexibility to the deck's strategy.

The deck focuses on utilizing aggressive creatures like Amped Raptor and Ranger-Captain of Eos, along with powerful spells such as Galvanic Discharge and Static Prison to quickly overwhelm the opponent. Ajani, Nacatl Pariah and Phelia, Exuberant Shepherd provide additional support and buffs for the creatures, while cards like Guide of Souls and Aether Hub ensure a consistent flow of mana. The inclusion of cards like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Arena of Glory adds versatility and strategic options to maintain pressure on the opponent.

This deck focuses on utilizing powerful Eldrazi creatures and control spells to dominate the game. The key strategy involves ramping up mana quickly with Eldrazi Temple and other lands, then using cards like Through the Breach and The One Ring to cheat out massive threats like Emrakul and Ulamog. Kozilek's Command and Ugin's Labyrinth help control the board, while Sowing Mycospawn provides additional value. The deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with big creatures and powerful spells, while maintaining control over the game.

This deck focuses on utilizing the Cascade mechanic to consistently cast Living End from the library to clear the board of creatures, enabling a powerful combo finish. The deck includes cards that manipulate the opponent's hand and graveyard, as well as disrupt their game plan. By strategically cycling through cards to set up the perfect cascade chain, the deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with a sudden board state swing and take control of the game. It combines control elements with explosive combo potential to secure victory in Modern 1 vs 1 matches.

The main focus of this Mardu Aggro deck is to quickly deploy aggressive creatures and disrupt the opponent's game plan with cards like Thoughtseize and Static Prison. The deck also utilizes powerful planeswalkers like Ajani, Nacatl Pariah to apply pressure and generate card advantage. Additionally, the deck features a mix of removal spells like Galvanic Discharge and threats like Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury to close out the game quickly. With a diverse mana base consisting of fetch lands and dual lands, the deck aims to have a consistent and aggressive game plan in Modern 1 vs 1 matches.

This deck focuses on utilizing Goryo's Vengeance to cheat out powerful creatures like Griselbrand and Atraxa, Grand Unifier from the graveyard onto the battlefield for a quick win. The combination of Fallaji Archaeologist and Tainted Indulgence helps to set up the graveyard with necessary targets for reanimation. Thoughtseize, Grief, and Priest of Fell Rites provide disruption and hand control. The deck also includes protection in the form of Solitude and Ephemerate. The mana base includes fetch lands and dual lands for consistency in casting spells. The deck aims to quickly assemble its combo pieces and overwhelm the opponent with its powerful threats.

The deck focuses on fast and aggressive plays, utilizing efficient creatures and direct damage spells to overwhelm the opponent. It includes a powerful Companion card to provide additional synergy and consistency. The strategy involves creating a board presence quickly with creatures like Amped Raptor and Guide of Souls, while using burn spells like Lightning Bolt to finish off the opponent. The deck also includes control elements like Static Prison to disrupt the opponent's game plan. Overall, the Mardu Aggro deck aims to apply constant pressure and close out the game before the opponent can stabilize.

This deck focuses on aggressive gameplay by utilizing efficient creatures and disruption spells to pressure the opponent and control the board. The deck also utilizes graveyard recursion with cards like Unearth and Gravecrawler to maintain pressure. Overall, the Golgari Aggro deck seeks to overwhelm the opponent with a combination of creatures, disruption, and resource management.
